    "description": "D. Western Therapeutics Institute, Inc., a biotechnology company, focuses on discovery and development of various drugs. It offers GLANATEC and GLA-ALPHA, an ophthalmic solution for the treatment of glaucoma/ocular hypertension; H-1337, a multi-kinase inhibitor that has started Phase IIb clinical trials for the treatment of glaucoma/ocular hypertension; DW-1001, an ophthalmic drug; and DW-1002, an ophthalmic surgical adjuvant for cataract surgeries, and ILM, ALC, ERM, and PVR membrane staining. The company is also developing DW-5LBT, a lidocaine patch for neuropathic pain after shingles; and DWR-2206, a regenerative medicine cell-product for bullous keratopathy. D. Western Therapeutics Institute, Inc. was founded in 1999 and is headquartered in Nagoya, Japan."
